com.amplifyframework.datastore

Interface DataStoreConflictHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataStoreConflictHandler.AlwaysApplyRemoteHandler, DataStoreConflictHandler.AlwaysRetryLocalHandler

    public interface DataStoreConflictHandler
    A hook to handle a conflict between local and remote copies of a model. The DataStore customer can implement their own version of this handler, and provide that handler to the DataStoreConfiguration while constructing the DataStore plugin using AWSDataStorePlugin.AWSDataStorePlugin(DataStoreConfiguration).

    • Nested Class Summary

      A handler which always elects to apply the remote version of the data.

      The possible decisions for a conflict resolution.
      static class  DataStoreConflictHandler.ResolutionStrategy
      An enumeration of the various strategies available for dealing with a model conflict.

      • onConflictDetected

        void onConflictDetected(DataStoreConflictHandler.ConflictData<? extends Model> conflictData,
                        Consumer<DataStoreConflictHandler.ConflictResolutionDecision<? extends Model>> onDecision)
        This callback method is invoked when the DataStore detects a conflict between a local and remote version of a model instance. Such a conflict may occur while the system is trying to upload a local change to the remote system. All code paths in the implementation of this handler must terminate by calling the provided consumer with a conflict resolution decision.
        Parameters:
        conflictData - Data about the conflict, including the local and remote copies of the model that are in conflict
        onDecision - An implementation of the DataStoreConflictHandler must end by invoking one of the resolutions on this handle.
